item.title: EV startup Ather seeks to raise $370 million in India IPO
item.description:
Indian electric scooter manufacturer Ather Energy plans to raise about $370 million by issuing fresh shares in an initial public offering, according to its draft prospectus filed on Monday (PDF), as the startup seeks to capitalize on growing demand for electric vehicles in the world’s third-largest auto market. item.title: 48 killed in fuel tanker collision in Nigeria
item.description: A tragic collision between a fuel tanker and another truck in Nigeria's Niger state led to an explosion, killing at least 48 people and burning alive 50 cattle. Search and rescue efforts are ongoing. The state's governor has called for calm among residents and emphasized the importance of adhering to road traffic regulations for safety.
